  "interpretation": [
    "The current lm-head W8A16 launch already uses the fastest probed workgroup size: 128 threads. 64 is ~2.1% slower on the isolated kernel; 256 and 512 are much worse from reduction/wave overhead.",
    "The current legacy shared-expert lowp W8A16 launches already use the fastest probed workgroup size: 64 threads. Larger workgroups regress both gate/up and down shapes.",
    "The existing fused shared gate/up+SiLU helper was probed as a decode-shape tile/fusion alternative; its best isolated median (~5.04 us at 512 threads) is slower than generic lowp gate/up at 64 threads plus the measured graph shared SiLU (~3.22 us + ~1.28 us), so it is not a c=1 decode replacement.",
    "Resource metadata shows no scratch, no SGPR/VGPR spills, low VGPR pressure, wave32, and tiny dynamic LDS reductions; the remaining lm-head cost is dominated by the unavoidable ~509 MB int8 weight stream per token, while the small shared linears are already launch/reduction efficient."
  ],
  "legacy_vs_packed_shared_expert_tradeoff": {
    "source_artifacts": [
      "benchmarks/results/2026-05-17-hipengine-qwen36-shisa-force-legacy-diagnostic.json",
      "benchmarks/results/2026-05-17-hipengine-qwen36-packed-shared-decode-fusion-diagnostic.json"
    ],
    "summary": "Forced legacy W8A16 shared expert is faster for shisa c=1 decode but worse for prefill and memory. Before packed-path tuning it improved decode by +7.4%/+7.2% at 512/4K while lowering prefill by -9.5%/-11.1%; after packed W4 decode recovery the remaining packed-vs-legacy decode gap is about -3.3% at both shapes. D5.2 found no W8A16 tile/occupancy win that changes this policy tradeoff; keep packed sidecars for packed checkpoints and legacy W8A16 only for legacy checkpoints."
  },
  "decision": {
    "action": "stop_no_code_change",
    "retained_defaults": {
      "HIPENGINE_QWEN35_LM_HEAD_THREADS": 128,
      "w8a16_linear_lowp_out shared-expert threads": 64
    },
    "rejected_probe_options": [
      "lm_head threads 64/256/512",
      "shared lowp threads 128/256/512",
      "c=1 shared_gate_up_silu replacement"
    ],
    "reason": "Target kernels are already occupancy/tile tuned for the decode shapes; remaining W8A16 time is dominated by bandwidth for lm_head and by graph launch/reduction floor for small shared linears."
  }
